HEADWORD: Philologer
<hw>Phi*lol"o*ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. L.
<ets>philologus</ets> a man of letters, Gr. <grk>filo`logos</grk>,
originally, fond of talking; hence, fond of learning and literature;
<grk>fi`los</grk> loving + <grk>lo`gos</grk> speech, discourse.]</ety>
<def>A philologist.</def> <rj><au>Burton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

